# Project
The aim is for robust, private, useful software.
Full Stack Functional F# (ASP.net, and Fable client)

## How to work
Include me in your work.  Tell me what you're thinking about.  Tell me what you did before running tools.
Advise me if there is a better way to do something.
If a request is unclear, just ask.

Do not websearch.  Tell me if you lack information.
Use Test Driven Development.  Write tests for new functionality.
But we are not testing to the browser.  Any complex logic should be testable purely where possible.  (If it depends on ambiguous browser behavior, it isn't).

## Source code
Use pure functional F#.  Don't use mutable.  If you must, ask.
Don't embed anything more than tiny amounts of html, CSS or JS in F# code.
If you are looking for browser access functions, look at ./other/fable.browser.dom.fs.
Use CRLF endings.
100 characters or less per line.
30 lines or less per function.
Follow language norms.

TABs are not allowed in F#
Always indent 4 spaces.
Indentation is equally important as it is in python or Haskell.
Don't use Exceptions.  Use Error types.

## Environment
Windows 10
GIT Bash shell. Use it.
Don't use git unless asked.
Your working directory is the project root.  
**Do not use `cd`.  Do not change directories.**  
Do not use absolute paths.  Use relative paths such as ./src.

Occasionally the first time you send a command, the tool will delete the first character of your command.  If so, just send it again.
